## B. Data correctness — grounding failures

### B1. Stale benchmark on fast-moving industries
**Severity:** P1 · **First observed:** Month 2 · **Status:** Mitigated

**Trigger.** Benchmarks for fast-moving categories (AI tools, crypto-adjacent businesses) drift faster than the quarterly refresh cadence.

**Symptom.** Outputs anchor to medians that are 6–12 months behind reality.

**Detection.** Per-industry `last_updated` timestamps surfaced in the API response.

**Mitigation.** Fast-moving industries are flagged with a `coverage_score` and a freshness disclaimer in the user-facing output. Refresh cadence for flagged industries moved from quarterly to monthly.

### B2. Regional cost data sparsity
**Severity:** P1 · **First observed:** Month 2 · **Status:** Tracked

**Trigger.** A user submits a business in a region with thin benchmark coverage (e.g., a city of 80,000 in the Mountain West).

**Symptom.** Cost estimates fall back to national medians without flagging that they did.

**Detection.** Coverage score per region is computed but not yet surfaced to the user.

**Mitigation.** Coverage transparency is a v1.1 scope item — every cost line will indicate whether it was anchored regionally, nationally, or industry-only.

