## What's open

- **Adversarial inputs.** A user who deliberately tries to break the model — contradictory descriptions, out-of-distribution business types, prompt-injection attempts in the description field — is currently handled by the schema validator, not by an explicit adversarial layer. This is on the Quantis 2.0 roadmap.
- **Multi-currency edge cases.** Non-USD currencies pass through but benchmark grounding remains USD-anchored. The real fix requires localized benchmark sets.
- **One-of-a-kind business types.** Concepts with no real industry analogue currently fall back to the closest archetype with a coverage warning. The better long-term answer is unclear; this may be a "no answer" case the product should refuse to attempt.

